{{Refimprove|date=December 2006}}
'''Automated Truck Loading Systems - ATLS''' has been commonly used in the material handling industry to refer to the [[automation]] of loading or unloading trucks and trailers with product either on or without [[pallet]]s, [[slip Sheet|slip sheet]]s, racks, [[Containerization|containers]], using several different types of [[automated guided vehicle]] systems (AGV) or [[engineering|engineered]] [[conveyor belt]] systems that are integrated into [[vehicle]]s, automating the [[shipping|shipping / receiving]] and [[logistics]] operations.<ref>{{citation|title=Inventory Accuracy: People, Processes, & Technology |author= David J. Piasecki|year=2003|publisher=OPS PUBLISHING|isbn=0-9727631-0-4}}</ref>
These conveyor systems are commonly referred to as {{col-begin|width=auto}} {{col-break}} *Roller beds *Slip chains *T-Bars *Live Floors {{col-break|gap=2em}} *Roller Tracks *Belt Floors *Trailer Skates *Skate & Tracks {{col-break|gap=2em}} *Slat Floors *Chain Floors *Cable Floors *Powered Cargo Rollers {{col-end}}
Some of these systems are used to handle [[bulk material handling|bulk]] products such as [[Waste|garbage]], [[agriculture]] products, recycled [[tire]]s, [[cotton]], bark or [[sawdust]]. Manufacturing industries such as automotive, food & beverage, paper, consumer products, appliance manufacturers and uses ATLS systems for incoming materials and outgoing product to increase throughput and streamline production. The transportation industry relies heavily on ATLS material handling systems to rapidly move product via land, sea, and air.
Next to solutions for palletised goods, Ancra Systems developed a custommade trailer unloading system for the automatic unloading of loose loaded parcels. The major advantages of this solution:
* Increased trailer loading capacity with 200% to 300% (no wheeled containers needed) * Trailer unloading time reduced to 25 minutes, which results in better trailer utilization * Reduced manpower * Increased ergonomics for workforce * Fewer docks needed (due to higher trailer loading capacity) * Maximizing sorting machines utilization * No forklifts needed, which means safer working environment<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ancra.nl|title=Automatic truck loading solutions - ANCRA SYSTEMS - Home|publisher=}}</ref>
ATLS vehicle loading technologies significantly reduce the manpower required on the shipping and receiving docks, eliminate product damage, accidents, and ergonomic injuries related to lift-truck operation. Generally, products can be loaded quicker and product density is increased resulting in more payload per shipment which reduces shipping cost, using a loading automation system. Loading automation is often the key component to achieve complete plant automation.
