'''Stash Financial, Inc.''', or simply Stash, is an American [[financial technology]] and [[financial services]] company based in New York, NY.<ref name="Forbes on Stash banking plans">{{cite web |first=Omri |last=Barzilay |title=Stash To Build Banking App "For All Americans" |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/omribarzilay/2017/11/09/peter-thiel-backed-stash-to-build-banking-app-for-all-americans/#127aa9765190 |website=[[Forbes]] |date=November 9, 2017 |accessdate=September 21, 2018}}</ref> Founded in February 2015 by Brandon Krieg, Ed Robinson, and David Ronick, the company launched its online investing platform in October 2015.<ref name="USA Today on stock market apps for students">{{cite web |first=Michael |last=Bodley |title=New apps make stock market affordable for students |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/college/2016/04/25/new-apps-make-stock-market-affordable-for-students/37416925/ |website=[[USA Today]] |date=April 25, 2016 |accessdate=September 21, 2018}}</ref><ref name="CNBC on Stash founding">{{cite web |first=Kathleen |last=Elkins |title=Wall Street vets left 6-figure jobs to launch an app that makes investing easy |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2016/10/21/wall-street-vets-left-6-figure-jobs-to-launch-an-app-that-makes-investing-easy.html |website=[[CNBC]] |date=October 21, 2016 |accessdate=September 21, 2018}}</ref> As of July 2018, Stash had approximately 2.4 million users.<ref name="KARE NBC 11 on Stash">{{cite web |first=Rena |last= Sarigianopoulos |title=Want to invest in the stock market? There's an app for that |url=https://www.kare11.com/article/news/want-to-invest-in-the-stock-market-theres-an-app-for-that/89-576697022 |website=[[KARE 11]] |date=July 24, 2018 |accessdate=September 21, 2018}}</ref>

